ZH: 我每天早晨都会诵经。
EN: I recite scriptures every morning.

ZH: 她经常在寺庙里诵经。
EN: She often recites sutras in the temple.

ZH: 他用慈悲的心诵经。
EN: He recites scriptures with a compassionate heart.

ZH: 我们需要专注地诵经。
EN: We need to recite scriptures with focus.

ZH: 他花了很多时间研究诵经的方法。
EN: He spent a lot of time studying the methods of reciting scriptures.

ZH: 我听到他声音洪亮地诵经。
EN: I heard him reciting scriptures with a loud voice.

ZH: 她愿意教我如何诵经。
EN: She is willing to teach me how to recite scriptures.

ZH: 他坚持每天晚上诵经半小时。
EN: He insists on reciting scriptures for half an hour every night.

ZH: 我希望能够有更多时间来诵经。
EN: I hope to have more time to recite scriptures.

ZH: 这位老师教导我们如何正确地诵经。
EN: This teacher teaches us how to recite scriptures correctly.

ZH: 他静静地坐在一旁诵经。
EN: He sat quietly on the side, reciting scriptures.

ZH: 她用优美的声音诵经。
EN: She recites scriptures with a beautiful voice.

ZH: 我们应该以诚心诵经。
EN: We should recite scriptures with sincerity.

ZH: 她诵经的速度非常快。
EN: She recites scriptures at a very fast pace.

ZH: 他们在宗教仪式中诵经。
EN: They recite scriptures during religious ceremonies.

ZH: 我感到平静和宁静当我诵经。
EN: I feel calm and peaceful when I recite scriptures.

ZH: 他全神贯注地诵经，没有任何干扰。
EN: He recites scriptures with full concentration, without any distractions.

ZH: 祖父教我如何正确地诵经。
EN: My grandfather taught me how to recite scriptures correctly.

ZH: 他喜欢在大自然中诵经。
EN: He enjoys reciting scriptures in nature.

ZH: 我们可以用这首颂诵经文。
EN: We can use this chant as a recitation scripture.
